You should know that what you are looking for is most likely Heraldric armor, imbued if you like.  This takes 3 blue diamonds if no fails, an imbued gem if you wish, about 4 blocks of velium, and some bought supplies to make a breastplate for.  You will need a smith with skill 225+ suggestable since it trivials over 250 and only a human can do the combine.  Also the tempers can be tricky to aquire but aren't hard after you get the essence of sunlight.<br>
<br>
There is a gap in AC for smithed armor.  30 ac acrylia, 32 ac with mosr stats Royal Imbued Velium (which is very expensive and used in a quest), 51 ac Heraldric with 40 hp/mana or so and stats if imbued.<br>
<br>
Since your a paladin you might want to talk to Blayze of League of Honor.  Many smiths have extra fees on the side if you collect the supplies or have large markups to protect their own intrests when it comes to cultural but I'm not sure if Blayze does or not.  Out of respect to the smith I would hope no one would have this type of armor made and then resell it for a profit.<br>
